{"altmetric_id":10093005,"counts":{"readers":{"mendeley":8,"citeulike":0,"connotea":0},"total":{"posts_count":21},"twitter":{"unique_users_count":19,"unique_users":["Q4LT00","BlameOxytocin","EJNeuroscience","JohnnyFoxe","idbravotobar","RelativeBrain","DrJKhokhar","jfasantosnet","neuroscience","psychologybook1","MirandaHeneghan","NathaniJo","NassufSavine","CamillesBijoux","corinna2010","Diane_Baudry","NewarkGuy","xiakai","MagdaYip"],"posts_count":21}},"selected_quotes":["New from EJN: Cocaine abstinence induces brain region-specific upregulation of oxytocin receptor binding","#addiction #cocaine #cerveau","RT neuroscience New from EJN: Cocaine abstinence induces brain region-specific upregulation of oxytocin receptor b\u2026","Cocaine abstinence = emotional impairment region-specific upregulation of oxytocin binding","Cocaine abstinence induces emotional impairment and brain region-specific upregulation of the oxytocin receptor\u2026"],"citation":{"abstract":"The key problem in treating cocaine addiction is the maintenance of a drug-free state since negative emotional symptoms during abstinence often trigger relapse. The mechanisms underpinning the emotional dysregulation during abstinence are currently not well-understood. There is evidence suggesting a role of the neuropeptide oxytocin in the modulation of drug addiction processes. However, its involvement during long-term abstinence from cocaine use remains unclear. In this study, we aimed to behaviourally characterize a mouse model of long-term cocaine withdrawal and assess the effect of chronic cocaine administration and long-term cocaine abstinence on the central oxytocinergic system and the Hypothalamic-Pituitary-Adrenal-axis. Fourteen-day escalating-dose cocaine administration (3 x 15-30 mg\/kg\/day) and 14-day withdrawal increased plasma corticosterone levels and oxytocin receptor (OTR) binding in piriform cortex, lateral septum and amygdala. A specific cocaine withdrawal-induced increase in OTR binding was observed in the medial septum. These biochemical alterations occurred concomitantly with the emergence of memory impairment, contextual psychomotor sensitization and an anhedonic and anxiogenic phenotype during withdrawal. Our study established a clear relationship between cocaine abstinence and emotional impairment in a novel translationally-relevant model of cocaine withdrawal and demonstrated for the first time brain region-specific neuroadaptations of the oxytocin system, which may contribute to abstinence-induced negative emotional state. This article is protected by copyright. All rights reserved.","altmetric_jid":"4f6fa4eb3cf058f610002841","authors":["Georgiou, Polymnia","Zanos, Panos","Hourani, Susanna","Kitchen, Ian","Bailey, Alexis"],"doi":"10.1111\/ejn.13348","endpage":"2454","first_seen_on":"2016-07-28T13:00:14+00:00","funders":["niehs"],"isbns":[],"issns":["1460-9568"],"issue":"7","journal":"European Journal of Neuroscience","last_mentioned_on":1477927344,"links":["http:\/\/www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\/pubmed\/27453431?dopt=Abstract&utm_source=dlvr.it&utm_medium=twitter","http:\/\/onlinelibrary.wiley.com\/resolve\/doi?DOI=10.1111\/ejn.13348#.V6sEH60dVn8.twitter","http:\/\/onlinelibrary.wiley.com\/resolve\/doi?DOI=10.1111\/ejn.13348#.V9dR00Qpz3M.twitter","http:\/\/onlinelibrary.wiley.com\/doi\/10.1111\/ejn.13348\/abstract;jsessionid=88EB3EF641C7452F49E31786C420B51C.f01t04#.V9dR00Qpz3M.twitter","http:\/\/onlinelibrary.wiley.com\/doi\/10.1111\/ejn.13348\/full?hootPostID=821c61452353beb5c5ad1b006f0f0f6c"],"pdf_url":"http:\/\/onlinelibrary.wiley.com\/doi\/10.1111\/ejn.13348\/pdf","pmid":"27453431","pubdate":"2016-07-01T00:00:00+00:00","publisher_subjects":[{"name":"Neurosciences","scheme":"era"},{"name":"Cognitive Science","scheme":"era"},{"name":"Psychology","scheme":"era"}],"scopus_subjects":["Life Sciences","Neuroscience"],"startpage":"2446","subjects":["neurology"],"title":"Cocaine abstinence induces emotional impairment and brain region-specific upregulation o